&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2 data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;WHO ARE WE&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cognism is the leading provider of European B2B data and sales intelligence. Ambitious businesses of every size use our platform to discover, connect, and engage with qualified decision-makers faster and close more deals. Headquartered in London with global offices, Cognism’s contact data and contextual signals are trusted by thousands of revenue teams to eliminate the guesswork from prospecting.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a practical, delivery-oriented Financial Systems Manager to own Cognism’s finance software stack, integrations and automation. You’ll be responsible for the finance systems that power core finance cycles including Quote-to-Invoice, Procure-to-Pay, Forecast-to-Budget, Hire-to-Retire, Compliance-to-Control and Asset-to-Depreciation. Our CRM is Salesforce and our ERP is NetSuite.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and run the finance systems roadmap - design, implement and maintain systems and integrations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead vendor selection, implementation and integration projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Automate core finance processes and build reconciliations between our CRM, ERP and other systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain data integrity, master-data governance and monitored integrations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create requirements, specs, and run UAT; deliver training and documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as first-line escalation for system incidents and own release/upgrade cycles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Finance, IT/Engineering, RevOps, HR and external vendors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Must have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years hands-on experience managing finance systems in a SaaS environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong NetSuite experience (configuration, integration, reconciliation) and Salesforce familiarity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise with middleware/iPaaS and APIs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical fluency with data (SQL/CSV/transforms) and automation (scripting/RPA).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track record running vendor implementations and delivering cross-functional projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent stakeholder management, documentation and training skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advantageous:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NetSuite admin or consultant certifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with subscription billing, FP&amp;amp;A tools, HRIS and AP automation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accounting qualification (ACCA/CIMA/ACA) or SOX experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h1&gt;
